Deputy President Cyril Ramaphosa says the ANC is now renewing itself and rebuilding so that supporters no longer feel hopeless. JOHANNESBURG - Deputy President Cyril Ramaphosa says the African National Congress (ANC) is now renewing itself and rebuilding so that supporters no longer feel hopeless. Ramaphosa has been on a two-day door-to-door campaign in the dissolved municipality of Nquthu this weekend. He says the ANC needs to change. An organisation that s renewing and repositioning itself... and wants to do things in a much more determined way. He says the ANC needs to rebuild for the people. An organisation that want to be stronger than it has ever been... that s the ANC. Ramaphosa also flew to Newcastle where he addressed a number of members, including former KwaZulu-Natal chairman Senzo Mchunu and former MEC Mike Mabuyakhulu.(Edited by Zamangwane Shange)